{
  "texts": [
    "Biron (2023) finds that posts from chatbots on a peer-based mental-health platform receive higher ratings than posts by humans, which is why transparency concerning the author is important.",
    "Wang et al. (2023) note ethical concerns about health care.",
    "Legal-ethical questions about responsibility in the case of patient harm are asked, as are questions about algorithmic ethics regarding bias, transparency, validation, and evaluation.",
    "New applications of ChatGPT in healthcare and psychotherapy are continuously being developed and explored, for example a yet unpublished tool for psychoanalytic interpretation of patient cases (personal conversation with Karl Golling on September 27 th, 2023).",
    "In summary, ChatGPT is considered a potentially useful tool in healthcare."
  ]
}